@jason-dai We only save one version of model which is based on the orignal BLAS backend. MKL-DNN layer is not visible to user. and can't use `saveModule` also. With @zhangxiaoli73 work, we can convert the original BLAS model at runtime based on the `engineType` property. 

But Int8 in MKL-DNN needs a model specific infomation (scales). They should be saved somewhere. This trait as a bridge between the two version of layers is a solution.  Then bigdl can save the scales in the model (protobuf).  and will sync them to dnn models when user call `quantize` and the engine is mkldn. 

Of cause, the initial version, only `Convolution` and `Linear` need the scales. But because of the optimization, the scales should be updated based on the fusion rules, such as conv + bn fusion will update conv's output scales to bn's output scales.

